Four armed robbers broke into a house on a farm near Paarl early on Tuesday, threatened the occupants and stole a firearm. “The circumstances surrounding a house robbery which was perpetrated this morning at around 6:30am on a farm in Klapmuts are under police investigation,” said police  spokesperson Lt-Col Andrè Traut. “Four armed suspects gained access to the house, threatened the occupants and fled with a licensed firearm. They are yet to be arrested.” A woman was allegedly assaulted during the robbery at Glen Gaul Farm. The incident follows another armed robbery on a farm in the Boland area. Stellenbosch wine farmer Stefan Smit was shot dead by masked intruders at Louisenhof Wine Farm on Sunday evening. This is a developing story.